{"title_page": "Comparison of digital image metadata editors", "text_new": "This article presents a comparison of [[digital image]] [[metadata]] [[File viewer|viewers]] and metadata [[Editor (disambiguation)#Computing|editors]].\n\nA metadata editor is a [[computer program]] that allows users to view and edit [[metadata tag]]s interactively on the computer screen and save them in the graphics file. Usually a metadata viewer is preferred over a metadata editor for viewing tags.\n\nA number of metadata editors for various platforms exist. Users choose among them based on factors such as the availability for the user's platform, the feature set and usability of the [[user interface]] (UI).\n\nThe [[Metadata Working Group|Metadata Working Group (MWG)]] is a consortium of leading companies in the digital media industry.<ref name=\"mwg\">http://www.metadataworkinggroup.org/info/pdf/photokina_pr_2008_09_24.pdf {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727082048/http://www.metadataworkinggroup.org/info/pdf/photokina_pr_2008_09_24.pdf |date=2011-07-27 }} Metadata Working Group Introduces First Specification for Interoperability and Preservation of Metadata in Digital Photography</ref> \nThe MWG publishes technical specifications that describe how to effectively store metadata into digital media files. These royalty-free specifications are made available to software developers, manufacturers and service providers so that they may create products that use metadata in a consistent way, and that allow consumers to better describe, organize and find their media. Where possible, these specifications rely on existing standards, and aim to create a unified and cohesive approach to applying these standards.<ref name=\"spec\">http://www.metadataworkinggroup.org/pdf/mwg_guidance.pdf {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120131102845/http://www.metadataworkinggroup.org/pdf/mwg_guidance.pdf |date=2012-01-31 }} Guidelines for Handling Image Metadata</ref>\n\n== Features ==\n\n{|  class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:80%;\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=2 | Software\n! rowspan=2 | Platform\n! rowspan=2 | License\n! rowspan=2 | Latest version\n! rowspan=2 | Last release year\n! rowspan=2 | Size<br />([[Megabyte|MB]]){{efn|The size depends on chosen installation.<br/>The lower limit is for a minimal installation.<br/>The upper limit is for a full installation with all features.}}\n! rowspan=2 | Description\n! rowspan=2 | Number{{efn|Number of editable tags}}\n! colspan=6 | Supported metadata standards{{efn|EXIF - Exchangeable image file format for digital still cameras<br/>\nGPS - The global positioning system<br/>\nIPTC - IPTC-NAA Information Interchange Model<br/>\nXMP - Extensible Metadata Platform<br/>\nMaker - Proprietary Maker Notes<br/>\nOther - Other standards, for example: IRB Adobe Photoshop image resource blocks, MPF - Multu-Picture Format\n:R - Can Read tags\n:E - Can Edit tags\n:W - Can Write tags\n:D - Can Delete tags}}\n! colspan=4 | Supported file formats{{efn|JPEG - ISO/IEC  IS 10918-1 1993(E)<br/>\nTIFF - Tagged Image File Format<br/>\nRaw - Proprietary raw formats<br/>\nOther - Other formats, for example: PSD Adobe Photoshop, DNG Digital Negative, JP2 JPEG2000\n:Yes - Format is supported}}\n|- \n! EXIF\n! GPS\n! IPTC\n! XMP\n! Maker\n! Other\n! JPEG\n! TIFF\n! Raw\n! Other\n|- \n| A Photo Manager<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/k3b/APhotoManager/|title=\"A Photo Manager\" with \"A Photo Map\", AndroFotoFinder|website=GitHub|date=24 May 2017|author=k3b}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A Photo Manager|date=24 May 2017|url=https://f-droid.org/repository/browse/?fdid=de.k3b.android.androFotoFinder|website=F-Droid|publisher=}}</ref>\n| Android\n| {{Free|GPLv3}}\n| 0.6.3.180211 (35) \n| 2018\n| align=\"right\"  | 1.3\n| Show/Edit GPS infos of local photos through a map.\n| {{dunno}}\n| {{partial|REW}}\n| {{Yes|REW}}\n| {{partial|R}}\n| {{partial|REW}}\n| {{partial|R}}\n| {{partial|R}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|